{
  "id": "MGASA-2021-0567",
  "summary": "Updated keepalived packages fix security vulnerability",
  "details": "In Keepalived through 2.2.4, the D-Bus policy does not sufficiently restrict\nthe message destination, allowing any user to inspect and manipulate any\nproperty. This leads to access-control bypass in some situations in which\nan unrelated D-Bus system service has a settable (writable) property\n(CVE-2021-44225).\n",
